  "riddle": "1. Seek the pioneer whose family tree branches from his standing — how many children did he call his siblings?\n\n2. Take the count of siblings from the previous find, and what do you get when you add its digits together?\n\n3. A historic residence known for its design stands at specific coordinates. What is the elevation of the abode nestled at 39°33′34″N 81°34′13″W?\n\n4. A sleepy town with a rich past holds a number regarding its land. What's the figure that describes its area?\n\n5. With your previous knowledge of this quaint community, discover how high the ground sits beneath its homes — what is the elevation of this town?\n\n6. Within a short distance from your previous location, how many libraries can you find nestled in the vicinity?\n\n7. By combining the elevation you found for the town and the count of libraries in your last clue, what new number emerges?\n\n8. Flowing gracefully nearby, this river passes as communities thrive. Count the churches that look toward the waters of this river.\n\n9. Visit the site known for its historic significance — what is the area of the distinguished residence that played a role in this town?\n\n10. Now, to find a single digit that completes your trail: compute the result of (clue 4 + clue 6 + clue 7 + clue 8), then take that sum modulo 10. What single digit do you arrive at?",
